Santa Clara County Sheriff Laurie SmithAllegations that Santa Clara County Sheriff Laurie Smith and some of her top brass traded concealed weapons permits to a private company protecting top Facebook officials in return for a large campaign donation have dogged Smith since July and August, when the Santa Clara District Attorney’s Office began serving search warrants on homes of top department officials and searched the sheriff’s headquarters.
That raises the prospect of someone or some organization trying to launder campaign contributions, which is a violation of state law.
San Jose Inside also reported last month that Santa Clara County Undersheriff Rick Sung had his home raided and some electronics confiscated by the DA’s office.
Report faults lack of standards on permitsMeanwhile, the San Jose Mercury-News reported last week that four Apple security executives had obtained concealed weapon permits.
The case of former Orange County Sheriff Mike Carona illustrates this.